node.text:
Reminder that it's the small daily habits that make the biggest impact on your life long term. Some things I've been trying to be mindful of and re-implement recently: 1.Workout/ move my body for at least 20 Minutes everyday. 2.Stop eating processed sugars, grab some fruit instead when you have an urge. 3.When allowing yourself to consume online content try to keep it educational. The internet is an incredibly powerful tool but it’s so easy to just use it for constant dopamine hits and become a zombie. 4. Whenever you feel like you “don’t have enough” (common emotion to feel in today’s society) return to a place of gratitude. If you can’t be grateful for what you have now, you’re not going to be grateful for what you will have in the future. 5. Daily Journaling and meditation is key to maintaining good mental health. 6. Drink more water. If I’m not proactive about it I catch myself going an entire day on very little water, so one thing I did was start carrying around a big bottle with me (40 oz) and make it a goal to finish that a few times each day. 
What daily habits are you trying to instill in your life right now?? 

Photos taken on the Namibian salt pans from my epic trip with @go_gravel_photosafaris @jandre_namibia_photo_ 🙏🏽♥️ shot on @djiglobal ‘s Air 2s drone.

node.text: 2 months ago if you had asked me to “roll my horse” or “tighten my girth” I would have had no idea what you’re talking about. I pretty much had zero knowledge of horses let alone how to ride them. But when @chelseakauai asked me to join her on a 180km 5 day journey on horse back across the Namibian desert I naively said yes, not knowing just how intense this journey was going to be. @piersonx and I both took a 3 hour lesson before embarking on this journey and managed to get the hang of it pretty quick. This was us on day 4 galloping full speed, no hands and Pierson holding a phone and stabilizer filming backwards lol. Definitely an experience unlike anything I’ve ever done before. I guess that’s why I loved it so much. More memories like this. Made possible by @ridingsafarinamibia @xcrossthewildx

We also have a lot of cool community contests and events planned the next couple of months. Enrollment is only open until July 1st so check the link in my bio if you’re interested in joining! 🙌🏽♥️

node.text:
An entire short film shot completely underwater......
I’m super excited to announce that @josiahwg just released his short film “Angelita” that @chelseakauai and I got to be a part of. Most of the film was shot 100ft (33m) down where a natural hydrogen sulphide layer sits. Everyday we would scuba dive down, take off all our scuba gear and then have a total of 15 minutes to shoot all the scenes we need before having to head back up. It was an insanely wild experience and it feels so good to see @josiahwg ‘s vision come to life. Also this wouldn’t have been possible without our incredible safety divers @tulum.breathtaking @camitorresph BTS video coming soon on my YouTube channel 🤘🏽head over to @chelseakauai or @josiahwg Instas to check out the full video!!!

This was a really special  getaway with @theroyalportfolio at the beautiful @royalmalewane . Check out the next clip to get a better look at the property through the eyes of my FPV drone!

node.text: This moment definitely stands out to me the most out of all the insane moments this past week at @royalmalewane . We were heading back to the lodge after a morning drive and saw some elephants hanging out on the road. We stopped about 40ft away and one of them curiously started to walk towards us. He ended up coming so close that I was told to raise my hand by our guide to get it to chill out and @piersonx was able to snag this pic 📸 truly an experience like no other being face to face with such a massive animal. Swipe to see some elephant goodness. 🐘 Thanks for the incredible experience @royalmalewane @theroyalportfolio everything from the service to the food to the amazing trackers and guides. Couldn’t have asked for a better trip! :) ♥️ shot on @canonusa @canoncanada R5 with 24-70mm :)
